          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-4">Beyond Compliance</h3>
            <p class="mb-4 text-gray-700">
              Traditional accessibility focuses on compliance. <strong>Trauma-informed accessibility</strong> recognizes that digital barriers mirror systemic exclusion and centers <strong>psychological safety</strong> in every design decision.
            </p>
            
            <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-purple-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-purple-700 mb-2">Core Principles:</h4>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                <div><strong>Safety First:</strong> Build trust rather than require it</div>
                <div><strong>Choice & Control:</strong> Users determine their engagement</div>
                <div><strong>Cultural Humility:</strong> Reflect diverse communication styles</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-purple-700 mb-3">Clinical Foundation</h4>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3">
              <strong>BA in Communication Sciences & Disorders</strong> + background in speech-language pathology and ABA brings deep understanding of:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-gray-700">
              <li>‚Ä¢ Neurodiversity and communication access</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Assistive technology integration</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Cognitive load and information architecture</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

